Make a donation to the Peru Earthquake Relief Fund!
Peru is beginning reconstruction after a powerful earthquake devastated the=
=20
southern region of the Andean highlands last Saturday. The 8.1-magnitude=20
earthquake, that has been recently upgraded to the "great" quake category -=
=20
the most powerful according to the U.S. Geological Survey- triggered a=20
tsunami that crashed into the seaport town of Camana destroying more houses=
=20
and raising the death toll. Up to now, the earthquake has left over 100=20
people dead, 1,374 injured and 47,696 homeless. The people who lost their=
=20
homes have been forced to sleep on the ground in Peru's frigid Andes=20
highlands, tents provided by the army and by some help organizations does n=
ot=20
provide sufficient issulation against winter temperatures in that region.=
=20
Help is urgently needed. If you would like to contribute to this cause plea=
se=20
send your donations to:

American Red Cross
2700 Southwest Freeway=20
Houston TX  77098
(In the memo line of your check please write: Earthquake-Peru, to ensure=20
funds are canalized correctly)

